# Spec 016 — Dual Workplaces: Shared Commute Intersection

Status: Draft
Owner: <you>
Related: 003/013 (band machinery + modes), 004 (hardening unchanged —
per-pin endpoints), 009 R5 (URL state), 015 R1 (per-pin address labels)

## Overview

Two-worker households don't ask "what can I reach from work" — they ask
"where can BOTH of us live." This spec adds a second work pin: each
location's reach is fetched independently (server caches stay per-pin), the
client intersects matching scenario bands, and the map shows only the area
inside BOTH commutes, with each pin's full reach kept as a faint dashed
context ring. The detail panel shows commute estimates to both workplaces.

## Requirements

- **R1 — Second pin.** An "Add second workplace" control creates pin B
  (draggable, A/B badges on both pins while dual); pin B is removable;
  switching states removes it. Address search gains an A/B target toggle,
  visible only in dual mode. Each pin shows its reverse-geocoded address
  (015 R1) in the work section.
- **R2 — Intersection rendering.** Per-pin isochrones are fetched through
  the existing per-location endpoint and intersected client-side by
  matching scenario (offpeak∩offpeak, typical∩typical, peak∩peak for
  drive; single∩single for walk/cycle). The intersection renders with the
  standard band styling; the reach line in the detail panel evaluates
  against the intersection.
- **R3 — Context + empty state.** Each pin's outermost band renders as a
  faint dashed outline for context. When no band survives the
  intersection, a visible message says so ("No area within both commutes —
  try a longer time or move a pin").
- **R4 — Dual commute estimates.** Selecting a ZIP shows estimate blocks
  for Work A and Work B (compact form — no departure-window parentheticals
  in dual mode). Single-pin display is unchanged.
- **R5 — Shared-reach areas.** In dual mode the traffic-scenarios fold
  shows the intersection band areas (client-computed) labeled as shared
  reach, with the shrink percentage recomputed from them; per-pin upstream
  areas are hidden.
- **R6 — URL state.** `lat2`/`lon2` (both-or-neither, validated, 4 dp)
  round-trip pin B through shared URLs, composing with 009 R5; any param
  still skips geolocation.
- **R7 — Hardening unchanged.** All upstream traffic flows through the
  existing per-location endpoints with their snap/cache/budget/rate-limit
  invariants. Dual mode roughly doubles per-interaction request counts;
  `RATE_LIMIT_UPSTREAM` is raised to 20/minute via env (render.yaml).

## Non-functional / Constraints

- Intersection via modular turf packages (`@turf/intersect`, `@turf/area`,
  `@turf/helpers` — sanctioned by the project stack; ~15 kB gz total;
  never the metapackage).
- Shared minutes/mode across both pins. Cost (24 h caches): dual drive ZIP
  selection = 12 calls; worst realistic dual session ≈ 12% of the daily
  budget — no budget change.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Add pin B across town: bands shrink to the shared area in standard
      styling, dashed rings show each pin's own reach; remove B → single
      mode restored exactly.
- [ ] Drag pins apart until nothing overlaps → the empty-intersection
      message appears; bands return when they overlap again.
- [ ] Selected ZIP shows compact A and B estimate blocks; reach line
      reflects the intersection; logs show 12 drive calls per fresh ZIP.
- [ ] Scenarios fold shows shared-reach mi² + recomputed shrink in dual
      mode; per-pin numbers absent.
- [ ] `?lat=…&lon=…&lat2=…&lon2=…` reproduces dual mode in a fresh tab; a
      lone `lat2` is ignored.
- [ ] `pytest` and `npm run test` green incl. the intersection lib tests;
      bundle delta noted (~15 kB gz).

## Out of Scope (explicit)

- More than two workplaces; per-pin minutes/mode (future work).
- Server-side intersection (would square cache cardinality).
- Sharing pin labels/names beyond A/B.

